56. What are all the Functions available to sort a PHP array?

Input:
<?php
// Sample arrays
$numbers = array(5, 2, 9, 1, 3);
$assocArray = array("d" => 4, "a" => 2, "c" => 9, "b" => 1);
$strings = array("img12", "img10", "img2", "img1");

// 1) sort()
$temp = $numbers;
sort($temp);
echo "sort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 2) rsort()
$temp = $numbers;
rsort($temp);
echo "rsort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 3) asort()
$temp = $assocArray;
asort($temp);
echo "asort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 4) arsort()
$temp = $assocArray;
arsort($temp);
echo "arsort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 5) ksort()
$temp = $assocArray;
ksort($temp);
echo "ksort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 6) krsort()
$temp = $assocArray;
krsort($temp);
echo "krsort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 7) usort()  – custom sort function (ascending)
$temp = $numbers;
usort($temp, function ($a, $b) {
    return $a <=> $b;
});
echo "usort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 8) uasort() – maintains index association
$temp = $assocArray;
uasort($temp, function ($a, $b) {
    return $a <=> $b;
});
echo "uasort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 9) uksort() – sorts by key using user defined function
$temp = $assocArray;
uksort($temp, function ($a, $b) {
    return strcmp($a, $b);
});
echo "uksort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 10) natsort() – natural order sort
$temp = $strings;
natsort($temp);
echo "natsort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 11) natcasesort() – case-insensitive natural order
$temp = $strings;
natcasesort($temp);
echo "natcasesort():\n";
print_r($temp);

// 12) array_multisort() – sort multiple arrays
$numbers1 = array(3, 2, 1);
$numbers2 = array("C", "B", "A");

echo "array_multisort():\n";
array_multisort($numbers1, $numbers2);
print_r($numbers1);
print_r($numbers2);
?>

Output:
