63. Discover a function that takes an array of numbers as input and returns the sum of all the even numbers in
the array.

Input:
<?php
function sumOfEvenNumbers($numbers) {
    $sum = 0;
    foreach ($numbers as $n) {
        if ($n % 2 == 0) {       
            $sum += $n;
        }
    }
    return $sum;
}
$arr = array(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6);
echo "Sum of even numbers: " . sumOfEvenNumbers($arr);  
?>

Output:
Sum of even numbers: 12

64. A retail company wants to forecast future sales based on historical data. Develop a system that utilizes
numerical types, mathematical operators to analyze sales trends, calculate growth rates, and generate
sales forecasts using arrays in php.

Input:
<?php
// Historical sales (e.g. monthly sales in USD)
$sales = array(12000, 13000, 15000, 17000, 18000, 21000);

echo "Historical Sales:\n";
print_r($sales);

// -----------------------------------------------
// 1) CALCULATE growth rates between periods
// -----------------------------------------------
$growthRates = array();
for ($i = 1; $i < count($sales); $i++) {
    // growth = (current - previous) / previous
    $growth = ($sales[$i] - $sales[$i - 1]) / $sales[$i - 1];
    $growthRates[] = $growth;
}

// -----------------------------------------------
// 2) Calculate the average growth rate
// -----------------------------------------------
$averageGrowth = array_sum($growthRates) / count($growthRates);

// -----------------------------------------------
// 3) Forecast the next period
// -----------------------------------------------
$lastSale = $sales[count($sales) - 1];
$nextSaleForecast = $lastSale * (1 + $averageGrowth);

// -----------------------------------------------
// 4) Output results
// -----------------------------------------------
echo "\nGrowth rates:\n";
foreach ($growthRates as $idx => $gr) {
    // multiply by 100 to show as percentage
    echo "Period " . ($idx + 1) . " growth: " . round($gr * 100, 2) . "%\n";
}

echo "\nAverage growth rate: " . round($averageGrowth * 100, 2) . "%\n";
echo "Last recorded sales value: $" . $lastSale . "\n";
echo "Forecast sales for next period: $" . round($nextSaleForecast, 2) . "\n";
?>

Output:
Historical Sales:
Array
(
    [0] => 12000
    [1] => 13000
    [2] => 15000
    [3] => 17000
    [4] => 18000
    [5] => 21000
)

Growth rates:
Period 1 growth: 8.33%
Period 2 growth: 15.38%
Period 3 growth: 13.33%
Period 4 growth: 5.88%
Period 5 growth: 16.67%

Average growth rate: 11.92%
Last recorded sales value: $21000
Forecast sales for next period: $23503.21

