67. Construct a program that tokenizes a sentence into words using regular expressions. Then, count the
number of occurrences of each word and display the results.

Input:
<?php
$sentence = "This is a test. This test is only a test."; 
$words = preg_split("/[^a-zA-Z]+/", strtolower($sentence), -1, PREG_SPLIT_NO_EMPTY);
$wordCount = array();
foreach ($words as $word) {
    if (isset($wordCount[$word])) {
        $wordCount[$word]++;
    } else {
        $wordCount[$word] = 1;
    }
}
echo "Word count:\n";
foreach ($wordCount as $word => $count) {
    echo $word . " : " . $count . "\n";
}
?>

